---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageHero from '../../components/PageHero.astro';

const city = 'Naples';
const slug = 'naples';

const localBusinessSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "LocalBusiness",
  "@id": `https://hugheyllc.com/florida/${slug}/#business`,
  "name": "Hughey LLC — Law Firm Marketing Consultant",
  "description": `Independent law firm marketing consultant serving ${city}, Florida. Strategy, attribution, and agency accountability for Collier County law firms.`,
  "url": `https://hugheyllc.com/florida/${slug}/`,
  "telephone": "+17274833222",
  "email": "joe@hugheyllc.com",
  "image": "https://hugheyllc.com/hughey-logo.png",
  "priceRange": "$$",
  "address": {
    "@type": "PostalAddress",
    "addressLocality": city,
    "addressRegion": "FL",
    "addressCountry": "US"
  },
  "areaServed": [
    { "@type": "City", "name": city },
    { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Collier County, FL" },
    { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Lee County, FL" }
  ],
  "founder": {
    "@type": "Person",
    "name": "Joe Hughey",
    "url": "https://hugheyllc.com/about/"
  },
  "sameAs": [
    "https://www.linkedin.com/in/joehughey/",
    "https://www.facebook.com/profile.php?id=61577138003264"
  ]
};

const breadcrumbSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
  "itemListElement": [
    { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://hugheyllc.com" },
    { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Florida", "item": "https://hugheyllc.com/florida/" },
    { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": city, "item": `https://hugheyllc.com/florida/${slug}/` }
  ]
};
---

<BaseLayout
  title={`Law Firm Marketing Consultant ${city}, FL | Hughey LLC`}
  description={`Independent law firm marketing consultant serving ${city}, Florida. Strategy and attribution for Collier County law firms serving Naples' high-net-worth client base.`}
  canonical={`https://hugheyllc.com/florida/${slug}/`}
  schema={[localBusinessSchema, breadcrumbSchema]}
>
  <div style="background: var(--ink); color: var(--white); min-height: 100vh;">
    <PageHero
      eyebrow={`${city} • Collier County`}
      heading={`Law Firm Marketing Consultant<br /><em>${city}, FL</em>`}
      subheading={`Independent strategy and attribution for ${city} law firms. A small, high-value market where most legal marketing playbooks fail because they're designed for volume, not relationships.`}
    />

    <div style="padding: 72px 0;">
      <div class="w">
        <div class="city-grid">
          <div class="city-body">
            <p>Naples is one of Florida's most distinctive law firm markets — small in population but exceptionally high in client value. Collier County has fewer than 1,500 active attorneys, but the per-matter economics here look more like Manhattan or Greenwich than the rest of Florida. Estate planning matters routinely involve eight- and nine-figure estates. Real estate transactions cross seven figures regularly. Business and trust litigation often involves out-of-state co-counsel and decades-long client relationships.</p>

            <p>For Naples law firms, the standard volume-based marketing playbook — lots of PPC, lots of forms, fast intake — is usually the wrong model. <a href="/">Independent marketing strategy</a> in Naples is about identifying the small number of channels that consistently produce high-value, referral-quality clients and ignoring the noise of generic legal-marketing automation.</p>

            <h2>The Naples Legal Market</h2>

            <p>Estate planning, probate, and trust administration dominate the Naples legal market. Collier County has one of the oldest median ages of any large county in Florida, with concentrated wealth in Pelican Bay, Port Royal, Old Naples, Quail West, and Mediterra. Estate planning firms here aren't competing for the average client — they're competing for the small subset of estates large enough to justify multi-day consultations, trust formation, and ongoing administration work.</p>

            <p>Real estate law is similarly skewed. Closings on Gulf-front properties, golf community homes, and Marco Island condos involve title work, contract review, and tax planning that generate far more revenue per transaction than the typical Florida residential closing. Business law, civil litigation, and family law all benefit from the same dynamic — fewer matters per year, but matters that justify deeper engagement and higher rates.</p>

            <p>Paid-search CPCs in Naples are moderate by Florida standards — "Naples estate planning attorney" runs $20–$40 — but those numbers are misleading. Click volume is low, and the highest-value clients almost never come through a paid ad. They come from referrals, country club relationships, financial advisor networks, and a small number of well-positioned content channels.</p>

            <h2>Why {city} Law Firms Work With Me</h2>

            <p>Naples firms come to me when their agency's standard playbook isn't working — or worse, when it's producing volume of unqualified leads that consume intake bandwidth without producing retained clients. The Naples-specific dynamics I look at:</p>

            <ul>
              <li><strong>Referral source attribution</strong> — financial advisors, CPAs, country club members, and existing clients drive most high-value matters; almost no CRM properly tracks these sources, so marketing budget gets misallocated to paid channels that look productive but aren't</li>
              <li><strong>Seasonal traffic and snowbird intake</strong> — Naples' population effectively doubles between November and April; firms that don't separate season from year-round attribution miss real performance trends</li>
              <li><strong>Out-of-state estate matters</strong> — many Naples estate planning clients have primary residences in the Northeast or Midwest; intake handling, conflicts checks, and co-counsel relationships matter more than lead-generation tactics</li>
              <li><strong>Reputation and review velocity</strong> — Naples is a small, networked community where reputation moves fast; a strategic GBP and review program produces more retained clients than most PPC campaigns ever will</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>What the Engagement Looks Like</h2>

            <p>A Naples engagement starts with the same analytics audit I do for larger-market firms, but with a different emphasis: instead of paid-channel optimization, we usually spend most of the first 60 days mapping referral sources, building proper CRM source attribution, and identifying the small number of content and reputation channels worth investing in. Most Naples firms cut their paid spend significantly within six months and reinvest in relationship infrastructure that produces better-fit clients.</p>

            <p>Engagements are remote, with on-site visits to Naples on a quarterly cadence when the work calls for it.</p>
          </div>

          <aside class="city-side">
            <div class="side-card">
              <h3>Service Area</h3>
              <p>Naples • Marco Island • Bonita Springs • Estero • Fort Myers • Pelican Bay • Port Royal • Collier and Lee counties</p>
            </div>
            <div class="side-card">
              <h3>Common Practice Areas</h3>
              <p>Estate Planning • Trust Administration • Probate • Real Estate • Business Law • Civil Litigation • Family Law • Elder Law</p>
            </div>
            <div class="side-card cta-card">
              <h3>Talk to Joe</h3>
              <p>Direct conversation about your firm's numbers. No sales pitch.</p>
              <a href="/contact/" class="cta-btn">Schedule a Free Call →</a>
            </div>
          </aside>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div style="padding: 64px 0; background: rgba(200, 151, 58, 0.05); border-top: 1px solid rgba(200, 151, 58, 0.15);">
      <div class="w">
        <div style="max-width: 760px; margin: 0 auto; text-align: center;">
          <h2 style="font-size: clamp(28px, 4vw, 40px); font-weight: 800; margin-bottom: 16px;">Ready to See Your Real Numbers?</h2>
          <p style="font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.72); margin-bottom: 32px;">If your Naples firm is spending real money on marketing without a clear picture of which channels produce retained clients, that's the conversation worth having.</p>
          <a href="/contact/" style="display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 9px; background: var(--gold); color: var(--ink); font-family: var(--man); font-weight: 800; font-size: 13px; letter-spacing: 0.07em; text-transform: uppercase; padding: 18px 36px; border-radius: 2px; text-decoration: none; transition: all 0.25s; box-shadow: 0 4px 28px rgba(200, 151, 58, 0.42);">
            Schedule a Free Call →
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <style>
    em { color: var(--glt); font-style: italic; }
    .city-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1fr) 320px;
      gap: 60px;
      align-items: start;
      max-width: 1180px;
      margin: 0 auto;
    }
    .city-body { font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.85; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.82); }
    .city-body p { margin-bottom: 24px; }
    .city-body h2 {
      font-size: clamp(24px, 3vw, 32px);
      font-weight: 800;
      color: var(--white);
      margin: 48px 0 20px;
      letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    }
    .city-body ul {
      margin: 0 0 24px;
      padding-left: 22px;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 10px;
    }
    .city-body li { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.78); }
    .city-body a {
      color: var(--glt);
      text-decoration: underline;
      text-underline-offset: 3px;
    }
    .city-body a:hover { color: var(--white); }
    .city-body strong { color: var(--white); font-weight: 700; }
    .city-side {
      position: sticky;
      top: 140px;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 18px;
    }
    .side-card {
      background: rgba(200, 151, 58, 0.05);
      border: 1px solid rgba(200, 151, 58, 0.18);
      border-radius: 4px;
      padding: 22px;
    }
    .side-card h3 {
      font-size: 12px;
      font-weight: 700;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.1em;
      color: var(--glt);
      margin-bottom: 10px;
    }
    .side-card p {
      font-size: 14px;
      line-height: 1.6;
      color: rgba(255,255,255,0.72);
      margin: 0;
    }
    .cta-card { background: rgba(200, 151, 58, 0.1); }
    .cta-btn {
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 6px;
      margin-top: 14px;
      background: var(--gold);
      color: var(--ink);
      font-family: var(--man);
      font-weight: 800;
      font-size: 12px;
      letter-spacing: 0.07em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      padding: 12px 22px;
      border-radius: 2px;
      text-decoration: none;
      transition: background 0.2s;
    }
    .cta-btn:hover { background: var(--glt); }
    @media (max-width: 900px) {
      .city-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
      .city-side { position: static; }
    }
  </style>
</BaseLayout>
